column2: These are the taxa that DO have WikiData entries, but my query/regex algorithm did not return the corresponding entry data––due to different spelling.
These are the taxa that DON'T have WikiData entries, so we manually assigned a Q-value to the taxa.
Repeats – these are the taxa that have two instances, and here I document the ones that I DID swap out – whether that be through a new WikData entry, or if none exists I made one up
